00:49:44.790 --> 00:49:47.390
We're also running a few tests
and collecting data, like

00:49:47.390 --> 00:49:50.500
incentivizing with SMS, calling
ahead of time, and

00:49:50.500 --> 00:49:52.450
then kind of comparing all
these different models to

00:49:52.450 --> 00:49:56.200
figure out what's the most
efficient way to do that that

00:49:56.200 --> 00:49:58.580
is least intrusive
to our users.

00:49:58.580 --> 00:49:59.640
So we have a lot of things.

00:49:59.640 --> 00:50:01.160
And I think we're a little
bit like you guys.

00:50:01.160 --> 00:50:02.950
We like to try a lot of things,
and collect data, and

00:50:02.950 --> 00:50:06.680
then go forward from that.

00:50:06.680 --> 00:50:09.530
AUDIENCE: So I noticed that
your organization really

00:50:09.530 --> 00:50:12.840
pushes using the market to
make great products.

00:50:12.840 --> 00:50:16.140
And I'm just wondering if
there's any collaboration with

00:50:16.140 --> 00:50:20.020
existing organizations like the
Red Cross that have tried

00:50:20.020 --> 00:50:23.240
to build a design that
isn't that great.

00:50:23.240 --> 00:50:25.470
And they have massive
resources,

00:50:25.470 --> 00:50:26.610
like a lot of people.

00:50:26.610 --> 00:50:28.440
They probably have distribution
channels that you

00:50:28.440 --> 00:50:30.560
don't have access to.

00:50:30.560 --> 00:50:32.390
So I was wondering if there's
any collaboration between

00:50:32.390 --> 00:50:37.380
D-Rev and larger nonprofits in
addition to the hospitals and

00:50:37.380 --> 00:50:39.650
other partners that you're
working with.

00:50:39.650 --> 00:50:41.920
VIN NARAYAN: I think the easy
answer for that is just that

00:50:41.920 --> 00:50:43.770
we're always open to
new partnerships.

00:50:43.770 --> 00:50:46.350
And for a group like that that
had the distribution channels

00:50:46.350 --> 00:50:48.470
in place, that would be a great
partner to work with.

00:50:48.470 --> 00:50:50.680
And so we're always open
to things like that.

00:50:50.680 --> 00:50:52.290
We're not working with
them right now.

00:50:52.290 --> 00:50:54.320
KRISTA DONALDSON:
We're trying.

00:50:54.320 --> 00:50:56.130
To answer your question
very directly is yes.

00:50:56.130 --> 00:51:00.110
We try and work with the best
people in the field, the best

00:51:00.110 --> 00:51:01.920
people with the best
distribution channels.

00:51:01.920 --> 00:51:03.010
I'll be honest.

00:51:03.010 --> 00:51:05.460
I feel like until recently they
were just like, oh, it's

00:51:05.460 --> 00:51:06.370
another student group.

00:51:06.370 --> 00:51:07.550
And we're like, we're
not students.

00:51:07.550 --> 00:51:10.075
We're actually developing
stuff, and

00:51:10.075 --> 00:51:10.820
they're getting used.

00:51:10.820 --> 00:51:13.040
So I feel like we're just
building credibility now.

00:51:13.040 --> 00:51:17.810
But yeah, I mean every time I
see certain leaders of other

00:51:17.810 --> 00:51:20.270
organizations that I know are
donating or buying devices,

00:51:20.270 --> 00:51:21.440
I'm like hey, have you
